name: r-framecleaner
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.2.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-framecleaner
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/framecleaner_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/framecleaner/framecleaner_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 97962975218eea27ff76b745eac5d91c437f5cf1affe8a18ac21a6a29bec94d1

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-bit64
    - r-dplyr
    - r-fastdummies
    - r-forcats
    - r-fs
    - r-janitor
    - r-lubridate
    - r-magrittr
    - r-purrr
    - r-readr
    - r-rio
    - r-rlang
    - r-rlist
    - r-rstudioapi
    - r-stringr
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyselect
    - r-vroom
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-bit64
    - r-dplyr
    - r-fastdummies
    - r-forcats
    - r-fs
    - r-janitor
    - r-lubridate
    - r-magrittr
    - r-purrr
    - r-readr
    - r-rio
    - r-rlang
    - r-rlist
    - r-rstudioapi
    - r-stringr
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyselect
    - r-vroom

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('framecleaner')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('framecleaner')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://harrison4192.github.io/framecleaner/, https://github.com/Harrison4192/framecleaner
  license: MIT
  summary: Provides a friendly interface for modifying data frames with a sequence of piped commands
    built upon the 'tidyverse' Wickham et al., (2019) <doi:10.21105/joss.01686> . The
    majority of commands wrap 'dplyr' mutate statements in a convenient way to concisely
    solve common issues that arise when tidying small to medium data sets. Includes
    smart defaults and allows flexible selection of columns via 'tidyselect'.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
